KARABO Mokoena&rsquo;s childhood friends have expressed their grief following her gruesome murder.They visited Karabo&rsquo;s home in Diepkloof, Soweto, yesterday. They were accompanied by ANC Women&rsquo;s League president Bathabile Dlamini and other league members.Karabo was allegedly murdered by her boyfriend of seven months, Sandile Mantsoe.&ldquo;I&rsquo;m still trying to come to terms with the fact that I&rsquo;ll never see my friend again,&rdquo; said Tshegofatso Sebolai (25), who lives just a few houses from Karabo&rsquo;s home. &ldquo;She was a bubbly person who enjoyed being around people.Another friend, Kholoza Ntlemeza (22), said: &ldquo;I used to share all my dreams with her. I feel cheated.&rdquo;Dlamini said Karabo&rsquo;s brutal death proves that we live in an angry, bitter community. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s painful because this shows that we&rsquo;re living in a patriarchal society where women will forever be victims.&rdquo;